I check about log structuration and the thing that come back the most is [The elastic suite](https://www.elastic.co/fr/products), which is `logstach + elasticsearch + kibana`. It read and parse your log files to json and send them to elasticserach, then kabina (the analytics dashboard) query the logs you've send to elasticsearch to render charts with your data.

My questions : 

* Do we really want to install such a huge stack
* Do we really need all these features ?
* Can we write our own and simpler stack for this kind of work?

