 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'davidsneighbour', 'comment_id': 753725635.0, 'datetime': '2021-01-04 02:31:59+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "I know it's splitting hairs, but per PHP documentation out of bounds `substr` returns false, not an empty string. That's probably because in PHP I would like to know WHAT went wrong instead of just going with what's coming back (nothing) from what I've done.

https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.substr.php#refsect1-function.substr-errors", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'zerovip', 'comment_id': 753732278.0, 'datetime': '2021-01-04 03:01:19+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Just as @username_2 explained, `echo false` prints an empty string in PHP. See, <https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.types.string.php#language.types.string.casting>.

----------

The PR LGTM. @username_2 , thank you for your work! And, @username_1 , @username_3 , thank you for your participating in the discussion!', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'davidsneighbour', 'comment_id': 753738255.0, 'datetime': '2021-01-04 03:29:12+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'If it's about that casting anything into a string will print an empty string if it's not already a stringable variable. A lot of these tickets here in the issue tracker are about "please don't throw an error if I do this" and half of the other tickets are "hugo is not throwing an error if I do this". Looks like Golang has an issue with typing :) As long as it's documented it's good.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
